<span id="freeTextContainer3945003096504718773">I found this a difficult book to read, both emotionally and cognitively, but it was, nevertheless, excellent and worth reading. It was recommended to me by a fellow blogger, and I folded it in to my 3-part prep-school bloc. It turned out to not have a lot of prep-school in it - mostly it&apos;s set in rural Georgia - but it was an effective use of contrast in showing the development of a child whose identity is kept from him until it&apos;s forced upon him. <br/><br/>FMI see my blog post at <a href='https://sloopie72.wordpress.com/2018/09/13/malcolm-hansen-they-come-in-all-colors-atria-2018/' target='_blank' rel='nofollow noopener'>A Just Recompense</a>.</span>
